    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
            
            $('.tab', '#section6').click(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $(this).addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).data('id') + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($(this).index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.tab-select', '#section6').change(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' +  ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.select .select-container div', '#section6').show();
                $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.record-slider', '#section6').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: true
            });

            function chkContentHeight() {
                $('p.description', '#section6').each(function() {
                    if($(this).height() > 160) {
                        $(this).parent().addClass('more');
                    }
                });
            }
            chkContentHeight();

            $('.record-item article button.view-more', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-less').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').show();
            });
            $('.record-item article button.view-less', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-more').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').hide();
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at IS?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="107">
                        <time>26/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Two talented students from Island School have been shortlisted for the prestigious Hong Kong Students Sovereign Art Foundation Prize! Sophie and Aahana, both from Year 12 have had their artworks selected.<br>This is a fantastic achievement and we encourage you to show your support by voting for their artworks below. Voting starts on the February 25th and ends on the March 29th.<br>Their work will be showcased at the prestigious art fair Art Central during Hong Kong's Art Week from March 25th - 29th, 2026.<br><br>Vote here:<br>https://www.sovereignartfoundation.com/sp-hongkong</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/f465138a0ac3db0f59d9185d1d7efade.jpg" alt="642091899_18448447195105991_3518194231387342843_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="106">
                        <time>16/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last week, we enjoyed Lunar New Year celebrations with parents, teachers, and students dancing in the courtyard. During our Lunar New Year assembly, we celebrated with student performances, face-changing acts, and a spectacular lion dance. <br><br>Happy New Year of the Horse, and Kung Hei Fat Choi!<br><br>Please note that the original music in this video has been modified for copyright reasons.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/238156c0d32ac7bcd64f2eab7ef1e6df.jpg" alt="633020393_18446882914105991_256582562127964703_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="105">
                        <time>06/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>After months of hard work, Harry Potter and the Cursed Child enchanted the stage at Borrett Theatre with four magical performances from February 3 to 5. Our talented students brought this beloved story to life, supported by an amazing production team.<br><br>A heartfelt thank you to everyone who attended and to Mr. McCracken, Ms. Kawano and Mrs. Lacey Vittachi for their incredible leadership and creativity, along with our dedicated technicians.<br><br>We look forward to more exciting events after the Lunar New Year Break, including our Spring Concert and IB Visual Arts Exhibition!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/437086f594cb1e207c454fd1f532cb83.jpg" alt="629459805_18444307390105991_1940315492246552702_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="104">
                        <time>06/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Einstein House successfully held their annual charity week from February 3-6, featuring a bake sale, Dress Purple Day, a Valentine’s Day delivery service, and live music in the courtyard where students dedicated songs to their valentines or expressed gratitude.<br><br>Since 1997, Einstein House has proudly supported Katja House, an organisation dedicated to helping underprivileged children in Kathmandu and rural Nepal.<br><br>Thank you to everyone who participated and contributed to this meaningful event!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/b92eb51b68fc674110c4bbd0a94956fb.jpg" alt="629462739_18444294715105991_5118738470692541295_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="103">
                        <time>30/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>On Friday, January 23rd, Island School hosted the postponed Winter Fair, and it was a lively and bustling event! Students showcased their talents in the courtyard and Performance Space, while the Sports Hall was filled with exciting games.<br>A huge thank you to all the parents and staff who volunteered their time and resources—your enthusiasm brought the fair to life!<br>Finally, thank you to everyone who attended. Your participation made it a memorable day and showcased the Island School spirit. See you all next year!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/53be46087ac877a83b83008584195121.jpg" alt="623095075_18442257733105991_1765430024700538140_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="102">
                        <time>30/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>On 23 January 2026, Islanders gathered for the annual Whole School Walk in support of the Island School Trust, which assists children in less privileged situations in Hong Kong and abroad.<br>Students showed off their creativity by dressing up as their favourite Disney characters and completing one of three trails: Bowen Road, the Harbour Front, or The Peak loop.<br>Congratulations to everyone who participated and donated.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/d6c4051cab1a22915c14159a1d6d46fa.jpg" alt="625033430_18442255771105991_6400713494797977215_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="101">
                        <time>23/01/2026</time>
                        <h3>On January 20th, we were thrilled to celebrate the resounding success of the Year 11 Social Action Exhibition. Since the start of this academic year, students have been immersed in group social action projects as part of their Global Perspectives IGCSE. This initiative, held under our Explorations programme, focuses on developing core competencies essential to future success in higher education and the modern workforce. By tackling key global issues firsthand, our students are truly evolving into informed global citizens.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4a7bb0bfd537aee04e6ae4359f57cf35.jpg" alt="621812329_18441034756105991_5174160940938780986_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="100">
                        <time>29/12/2025</time>
                        <h3>An ESF Christmas story that melted hearts: Meet Cassidy, a student from ESF Glenealy School with proud Fijian and Scottish heritage. Cassidy dreamed of becoming a vet one day.<br><br>Her Christmas letter found its way to a mystery person at ESF Island School, Kanna — and what happened next was pure holiday magic.<br><br>This is what the ESF community is all about — sharing love, laughter, and friendship across our schools. Wishing everyone a wonderful Christmas break.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/0ce3540460ae8d446d092719ff61465c.jpg" alt="608206300_18437790721105991_5853909472722121340_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="99">
                        <time>17/12/2025</time>
                        <h3>As we wrap up another incredible term at Island School, the last day before the Christmas holidays is always a highlight!<br><br>This year, the BTEC Dance Group wowed us with their fantastic performance, and we enjoyed amazing acts from Jayden, the winner of STARS, who sang his winning song "It Had Better Be Tonight," along with Amoures performing "A Sky Full of Stars."<br><br>Keeping with tradition, our teachers and Year 13 students took the stage to sing "Hark! The Herald Angels Sing" and "We Three Kings." Before long, the whole school was jumping, hugging, and singing along to Slade's "Merry Christmas Everybody."<br><br>Wishing everyone a joyful holiday season! We can't wait to see you all in 2026!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/cea3f1386af2ef9d4d1e41b9119fc14d.jpg" alt="601776471_18436278583105991_5899271246645852885_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="98">
                        <time>17/12/2025</time>
                        <h3>This year's Christmas celebrations at Island School were a delightful festive occasion, held from December 9-12! The holiday spirit was alive, with Christmas music playing and karaoke during breaks. Activities included the PTA Plush Sale, Elements Marketplace, Christmas cookie decoration, and the Senior Phase Christmas Quiz, where Fleming house emerged as the winner.<br>Funds raised from all the events will go toward supporting the Tai Po Relief Fund.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/9228718c152cb0fb4f4999f5784e3acc.jpg" alt="601438282_18436278121105991_8616789884568789357_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
